Above the Ordinary

I am on the wind
f l y i n g  when I close my eyes
catching the air
with arms that become wings
free
as a child playing make believe
s o a r I n g 
above the ordinary
cutting loose the pull of 
gravity
no anchor
to force rules or limits
no anchor
to weigh down my dreams

Midnight Musings by 
Tammi Brown
2019
